<apex:page controller="FimbySupporteeActivationLetterController"
           renderAs="pdf"
           applyHtmlTag="true"
           showHeader="false"
           sidebar="false"
           standardStylesheets="false"
           docType="html-5.0"
           cache="false"
           contentType="application/pdf">
<head>
    <style type="text/css">
        @page { size: letter; margin: 0.9in; }
        body {
            font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 12pt;
            color: #2a2a2a;
            line-height: 1.55;
        }
        .from {
            font-size: 10pt;
            color: #555;
            margin-bottom: 30pt;
        }
        .to {
            white-space: pre;
            margin-bottom: 28pt;
        }
        .greet { margin: 0 0 14pt; }
        p { margin: 0 0 12pt; }
        .signoff { margin-top: 24pt; }
        .footer {
            font-size: 9pt;
            color: #555;
            margin-top: 28pt;
            border-top: 1pt solid #cfcfcf;
            padding-top: 8pt;
        }
        .err { color: #b00020; font-weight: 600; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<apex:outputPanel rendered="{!hasError}">
    <p class="err">{!errorMessage}</p>
</apex:outputPanel>

<apex:outputPanel rendered="{!NOT(hasError)}">
    <div class="from">
        FIMBY (Family In My Backyard)<br/>
        help@fimby.com<br/>
        {!renderedDate}
    </div>

    <div class="to">{!supporteeAddressBlock}</div>

    <p class="greet">Hello {!supportee.FirstName},</p>

    <p>You're receiving this letter because <strong>{!supporter.Name}</strong> set up a
    FIMBY supporter relationship on your behalf in {!sr.Neighbourhood__r.Name}.
    They told us you signed a paper authorization form, and our team approved it
    on {!approvedDateLabel}.</p>

    <p><strong>What this means:</strong> {!supporter.FirstName} can now post asks and
    offers, reply to neighbours, and use the FIMBY library on your behalf. They
    cannot change your password, delete your account, or sign anything outside FIMBY.</p>

    <p><strong>If you did not sign this form, or you've changed your mind:</strong> please
    call or email us. We will end this relationship immediately, no questions asked.
    You don't need to give a reason. Reach us at <strong>help@fimby.com</strong>.</p>

    <p>If everything is as you expected, you don't need to do anything — this letter
    is just for your records.</p>

    <p>Thanks for being part of your neighbourhood.</p>

    <p class="signoff">— The FIMBY team</p>

    <p class="footer">
        Reference: {!sr.Name}.
        FIMBY always confirms with the person being supported, not just the supporter.
        That's why you're getting this letter.
    </p>
</apex:outputPanel>
</body>
</apex:page>
